c:3997.name: OFR Financial Stress Index
c:3997.description:
Financial Stress Index (FSI) is created by Office of Financial Research (OFR), using 33 financial variables out of five categories: credit, equity, funding, flight to safety, and volatility. It reflects the stress level the financial market goes through everyday.

When the index equals zero, the variables are at their long-run average. When the index is positive, financial risks are rising. When it's negative, the market is comparatively steady and safe.
